Pidgin is an easy to use and free chat client used by millions. Connect to AIM, Google Talk, ICQ, IRC, XMPP, and more chat networks all at once.

== Installation ==

=== USE flags ===

{{USEflag|package=net-im/pidgin}}

=== Emerge ===

{{Emerge|net-im/pidgin}}

== Configuration ==

Pidgin's [https://developer.pidgin.im/wiki/Using%20Pidgin guide] is a complete guide through the process of configuring every aspect of pidgin. 

An ''' important ''' consideration is that Pidgin configuration files are saved in plain text, so it's recommendable to use unique passwords for the accounts or always connect without saving the password.

== Usage ==

Pidgin comes with a GUI based on Gtk that lets you interact with different protocols and stay connected to different servers as described in the Pidgin's [https://developer.pidgin.im/wiki/Using%20Pidgin guide]

== Plugins ==

Pidgin has a community of third-party developed plugins. You can find out more on the third party plugins at the [https://developer.pidgin.im/wiki/ThirdPartyPlugins official wiki page].

== Removal ==

=== Unmerge ===

{{Emerge|-C net-im/pidgin}}

=== Configuration and logs ===

After unmerging, for a full clean-up, be sure to remove old logs and individual user configuration from their default location in each {{c|pidgin}} user's home directory:

{{Cmd|rm -rf ~/.purple}}

